      • mapDifferences

        public static IGraph<Diff> mapDifferences(Collection<Diff> differences,
                                          IMerger.Registry mergerRegistry,
                                          boolean mergeRightToLeft,
                                          MergeMode mergeMode)
        This will map the given differences in a dependency graph, enabling EMF Compare to differentiate what can be safely merged from what cannot.

        Typically, all differences that are not in a real conflict with another and that do not depend, directly or indirectly, on a conflicting difference can be pre-merged without corrupting the models. For example, if adding a reference "ref1" to an added class "C1" depends on the addition of a package "P1" (i.e. three additions in a row), but "C1" has also been added in another place in the other model (a conflict between two "same" elements added into different containers), then we can safely pre-merge the addition of P1, but not the addition of its contained class C1, nor the addition of ref1.

        Parameters:
        differences - The differences to be mapped into a dependency graph.
        mergerRegistry - The merger registry currently in use.
        mergeRightToLeft - The direction in which we're preparing a merge.
        mergeMode - The merge mode. If MergeMode is null, then no differences will be filtered.
        Returns:
        The dependency graph of this comparison's differences.

      • getAllResultingMerges

        public static Set<Diff> getAllResultingMerges(Diff diff,
                                              IMerger.Registry mergerRegistry,
                                              boolean mergeRightToLeft)
        Retrieves the set of all diffs related to the given diff when merging in the given direction.

        This is expected to return the set of all differences that will be need to merged along when a user wishes to merge diff, either because they are required by it or because they are implied by it one way or another.

        Note that diff will be included in the returned set.

        Parameters:
        diff - The difference for which we seek all related ones.
        mergerRegistry - The merger registry currently in use.
        mergeRightToLeft - The direction in which we're considering a merge.
        Returns:
        The set of all diffs related to the given diff when merging in the given direction.

        Retrieves the set of all diffs that will be rejected if the given diff is merged, either because of unresolveable conflicts or because of unreachable requirements.
        Parameters:
        diff - The difference for which we seek all opposite ones.
        mergerRegistry - The merger registry currently in use.
        mergeRightToLeft - The direction in which we're considering a merge.
        Returns:
        The set of all diffs that will be rejected if the given diff is merged in the given direction.
